Awhile back I stopped Tweeting for 3-4 months.
I dont use Twitter to market . Frankly most on Twitter are uninterested in subscription services that cost ++$s
I send out useful readings and when my RealMoneyPro articles go to the free TST flagship site I send those out as well.
But sometimes it just feels like it isnt worth my time - to be blunt and to state the obvious.
I have learned to navigate the Twiiter waters and to ignore the sharks/haters in order to find the nice fish.
I tweet to exchange information (so I can be a better trader/investor) and to help out some who elect not to or cant afford sub services.
Every two to three months or so I ask why do I even bother to Tweet? How am I benefitting? This is one of those times.
